  "prompt": "Which are the top 5 Bollywood songs of 2015?",
  "response": "In 2015, Bollywood produced several memorable songs that became immensely popular. While opinions on the \"top\" songs can vary, here are five of the most loved and widely recognized Bollywood songs from that year:\n\n1. **\"Gerua\"** - *Dilwale*  \n   Sung by Arijit Singh and Antara Mitra, this romantic track, composed by Pritam, became a huge hit for its mesmerizing melody and stunning visuals featuring Shah Rukh Khan and Kajol.\n\n2. **\"Agar Tum Saath Ho\"** - *Tamasha*  \n   Sung by Arijit Singh and Alka Yagnik, this soulful song, composed by A.R. Rahman, touched hearts with its emotional depth and meaningful lyrics.\n\n3. **\"Deewani Mastani\"** - *Bajirao Mastani*  \n   Composed by Sanjay Leela Bhansali and sung by Shreya Ghoshal, this grand and opulent track captured the essence of the epic love story in the film.\n\n4. **\"Jaan Nisar\"** - *Khamoshiyan*  \n   Sung by Arijit Singh, this hauntingly beautiful track, composed by Jeet Gannguli, became a fan favorite for its unique melody and eerie vibe.\n\n5. **\"Naam Shabana\"** - *Baby*  \n   Sung by various artists including Benny Dayal, Neeti Mohan, and others, this energetic and empowering track, composed by Meet Bros, was widely loved for its catchy tune and upbeat rhythm.\n\nThese songs not only dominated the charts but also remained popular long after their release.",
